Rating: 4
Delicious. After reading through the other reviews I bumped up the heat to 365, and baked it for about 48 minutes at that heat. I also did it in a cast-iron pan (the same that I used to fry the chorizo in, and used that fat to grease the pan instead of butter), which seemed to put a nice crust on the outside rim. I cut it about 10 minutes after it came out of the oven, and let the pieces cool on racks individually, rather than in the pan. It dried it up some, and made it a more familiar cornbread consistency, while still retaining the moisture in the middle. I also used sour cream instead of yogurt.

